record.title: AUTHORIZING THE CLERK TO MAKE CORRECTIONS IN ENGROSSMENT OF H.R. 2669, COLLEGE COST REDUCTION ACT OF 2007
record.narrative:
AUTHORIZING THE CLERK TO MAKE CORRECTIONS IN ENGROSSMENT OF H.R. 2669, COLLEGE COST REDUCTION ACT OF 2007 -- (House of Representatives - July 11, 2007)

[Page: H7559]

speaking.paragraph: Mr. Speaker, I ask unanimous consent that, in the engrossment of the bill, H.R. 2669, the Clerk be authorized to correct section numbers, punctuation, citations, and cross references and to make such other technical and conforming changes as may be appropriate to reflect the actions of the House.

record.chair: Is there objection to the request of the gentlewoman from New York?
